{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01HA43gREVWvUjhrpR7w9TKq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01AZjs9EptRQe8DRv6juQ27J","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Invalid signature (mismatch with body) is rejected with 401; body not forwarded to queue","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failures live in HTTP request body capture (raw bytes, encoding issues), signature comparison logic, and queue integration. Unit tests of isolated crypto functions miss raw-body encoding bugs and whether rejection prevents forwarding. Must test with real HTTP request object (preserving raw body for signature calculation) wired to both signature validation and queue integration.","test_description":"Send HTTP POST with intentionally mismatched X-Signature-256 header (e.g., header contains SHA256 of body+'tampered'). Verify 401 returned and queue.enqueue() never called. Then send same body with correct signature, verify 200 and event in queue.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Integration catches the critical intersection: raw body handling + signature validation + queue prevention.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.85,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Event is written to persistent queue before HTTP 200 acknowledgment is returned","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a race condition between two I/O operations: queue.write() and response.send(). Can't test at Unit (no I/O). Must wire handler, queue client, and HTTP response together. The critical failure is 200 being sent before queue confirms write. A test-double queue that tracks completion order and a real HTTP test server capture this. Note: If the persistent queue is an external broker (Kafka/RabbitMQ with network latency), System testing may expose real failures that Integration with a local queue misses